           <img alt="International Mountain Studies Symposium" src="/_images/_events/2019/spring/international-mountain-studies-symposium-hmajors-2000.jpg"/>
          </picture>
         </a>
        </figure>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="hmajors-03">
      <div class="hmajors-04">
       <div class="hmajors-05">
        <div>
         <div>
          <div class="hmajors-left">
           <div>
            <div class="hmajors-title">
             <a href="https://appstudies.appstate.edu/international-mountain-studies-symposium" target="_blank">
              International Mountain
              <span style="white-space: nowrap;">
               Studies Symposium
              </span>
             </a>
            </div>
            <div class="hmajors-subtitle">
             <p>
              Tuesday, March 12, 2019
              <br/>
              Keynote speakers: Jon Mathieu, Gilles Rudaz and Dawn Hollis
              <br/>
              Plemmons Student Union
             </p>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hmajors-right">
           <div>
            <div class="hmajors-teaser">
             <p>
              This symposium will bring mountain studies scholars from around the globe to present their research alongside members of our campus community—advanced undergraduate students, graduate students, faculty and staff—focusing our campus’s attention on comparative mountain studies between the Appalachian Mountains and other mountain regions around the world.
             </p>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
