                   Jessica Reed: World, Composed
                  </a>
                 </div>
                 <div class="events-subtitle">
                  <p>
                   2019 Bivens Occasional Lecture on the Scholarship of Books and Readings
                  </p>
                 </div>
                 <div class="events-date-02">
                  Thursday, March 14, 2019
                 </div>
                 <div class="events-date-03">
                  5 p.m.
                 </div>
                 <div class="events-teaser">
                  <p>
                   The University Libraries at Appalachian State University presents World, Composed, a reading by poet Jessica Reed. Reed’s first collection of poetry,
                   <em>
                    World, Composed
                   </em>
                   , takes exquisite aim at the universe of physics in all its complexity. Hers is a voice of scientific authority and poetic innovation, in literary conversation with the ancient poet Lucretius, who first explored the existence of atoms in verse.
                  </p>
                 </div>
